<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>It seems like the good things are all hitting at once for Usher Raymond. </p>

<p>Not only is the eight-time Grammy winner expecting his third child with his new love Jenn Goicoechea, but the star also took to his Instagram on Friday to announce some more exciting news. </p>

<p>Usher announced via social media that he will begin his residency in Las Vegas at Caesars Palace Colosseum starting in July 2021 - which sent his 8.9M followers buzzing. </p>

<p>Yeah!: Usher Raymond, 41, took to Instagram on Friday to announce his Las Vegas residency in July of 2021 at Caesars Palace Colosseum</p>

<p> 'I’ll be kicking off my Vegas residency July 2021 at Caesars Palace Colosseum!' the star wrote. </p>

<p>'Tickets go on sale Thursday 9/10 at 10 AM PT, but you can get yours starting Monday if you text me at (404) 737-1821. I’ll hit you back with the presale code this weekend. For all dates and tickets head to www.ticketmaster.com/ushervegas' he continued in his caption. </p>

<p>The Las Vegas residency is a rite of passage for many huge performers with notable stars like Jennifer Lopez, Celine Dion and Britney Spears having all done them for large sums of money. </p>

<p>Triple threat: The Las Vegas residency is a right of passage for many huge performers with past acts including Jennifer Lopez and Celine Dion</p>

<p>Up and away: The eight-time Grammy winner is starting a new chapter in his career with the announcement of his new residency in Sin City; February 2020</p>

<p>The 41-year-old triple threat will put his incredible dancing and singing skills on display for what is sure to be a spectacle that many fans will flock to. </p>

<p>'I have missed performing for my fans live and I am so excited to see them in Las Vegas,' Usher said in a statement on Caesars website. </p>

<p> 'My residency at The Colosseum at Caesars Palace will be full of surprises and an Usher experience like they've never seen or heard before' he concluded. </p>

<p>This is the first Las Vegas residency to be announced since the COVID-19 pandemic. </p>

<p>Though the future of live entertainment is uncertain, Caesars Palace and Sin City are holding out hope that things will be able to return to normal by next summer.  </p>

<p>In addition to this exciting new career venture Usher is also expecting his third child with his new partner, Jenn Goicoechea.  </p>

<p>Baby on board: Usher Raymond and his girlfriend of a year Jenn Goicoechea attend Paris Fashion Week. The couple are expecting their first child together; February 2020</p>

<p>Speaking to Us Weekly a close source of the pair reported that 'They are thrilled and very excited.' </p>

<p>The pair were first linked last Fall after they were seen canoodling at the Hollywood Bowl before attending Sean 'P Diddy' Combs 50th birthday party back in December. </p>

<p>Raymond has two children Naviyd Ely, 11 and Usher V, 12 with his ex-wife Tameka Foster to whom he was married for two years before splitting in 2009.</p>

<p>Since quarantine Usher has been spending a lot of time with his boys and girlfriend as they prepare to expand their family by one. </p>

<p>Back in May the star took part in Verizon's Pay it Forward Live series to support small businesses affected by the COVID-19 pandemic.</p>

<p>Dad of 3: Within weeks of each other Usher had confirmed that he was expecting a child with his girlfriend and preparing for a Vegas residency in July 2021; RocNation Brunch, January 2020</p>
